'''Mohammad Faisal Yousef Abu Zrayq''' ({{langx|ar|محمد فيصل يوسف أبو زريق}}, born 30 December 1997), popularly known as '''Sharara''' ({{langx|ar|شرارة}}), is a Jordanian professional footballer who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Botola Pro]] club [[Raja CA]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
He started his career for [[Al-Ramtha SC|Al-Ramtha]] and was loaned to [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]] in the summer of 2019.<ref>[https://www.kooora.com/?n=823800&o=n3059519 The Koora website statements by Mohammed Sharara "I will play in Jordan only for Ramtha" published on 16-6-2019] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217032242/https://www.kooora.com/?n=823800&o=n3059519 |date=17 December 2019}}</ref>
On 9 January 2022, he joined Libyan club [[Al Ahli SC (Tripoli)|Al Ahli]] on a free transfer.
On 15 August 2022, he joined Tunisian club [[Espérance Sportive de Tunis|Espérance de Tunis]], in a three-year deal. On 3 December 2023, he made his return to [[Al Ahli SC (Tripoli)|Al Ahli]] for 3 months before joining hometown club [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al Wehdat]]. On 30 July 2024, Sharara joined [[Iraq Stars League]] side [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]].<ref>{{cite web |title="شرارة" ينضم لنادي الشرطة العراقي |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%B6%D9%85-%D9%84%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-1774775 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |language=Arabic |date=30 July 2024}}</ref> On 30 January 2025, he joined [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يتعاقد مع شرارة |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1385527 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=1 February 2025 |language=Arabic |date=30 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=شرارة يعود إلى الدوري الأردني من بوابة البطل.. مهمة كبيرة بانتظاره مع الحسين |url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/sport/%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%85%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A9-%D9%83%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%B8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%87 |website=alaraby.co.uk |publisher=The New Arab |access-date=1 February 2025 |language=Arabic |date=31 January 2025}}</ref>

===Return to Al-Ramtha===
On 20 July 2025, [[Al-Ramtha SC|Al-Ramtha]] announced the signing of Sharara on a one-year, free transfer from [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]].<ref>{{cite web |title=رسمياً.. "شرارة" يدعم هجوم الرمثا |url=https://www.kooora.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B9%D9%85-%D9%87%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7/bltddb82f968eba51b0 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=20 July 2025 |language=Arabic |date=20 July 2025}}</ref>

===Raja CA===
On 5 January 2026, Sharara joined [[Botola Pro]] club [[Raja CA]], after terminating his contract with [[Al-Ramtha SC|Al-Ramtha]].<ref>{{cite web |title=رسمياً.. الرمثا الأردني يعلن رحيل شرارة إلى الرجاء المغربي |url=https://www.kooora.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%8B--%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%94%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%95%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A/blt7e82392737e35bac |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=5 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=خاص  تفاصيل جديدة بشأن اتفاق الأردني شرارة مع الرجاء المغربي |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%AA%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B5%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A9%C2%A0%D8%A8%D8%B4%D8%A3%D9%86-%D8%A5%D8%AA%D9%81%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWIn |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=5 January 2025}}</ref>

==International career==

Sharara played his first international match with the Jordan national team against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] in a friendly match on 7 June 2019. He was named in Jordan's squad for the [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]].

